      <h2>Windy City Night</h2>
      <p>Chicago’s distinction as the Windy City doesn’t just refer to its blustery weather. From the Tribune to the Sun Times, Chicago has a long history of exceptional, though sometimes long-winded, storytelling. Genre-defining writers like Roger Ebert and Studs Terkel have called Chicago home, while the Second City continues to serve as a launching pad for some of the best and most respected storytellers like Tina Fey, Stephen Colbert, and Amy Poehler.</p>
      <p>For the event’s final night, Lea Thau will host a training session to help improve communication and storytelling skills. Thau is a Peabody Award-winning producer and director who created and hosted Strangers and the immensely popular Moth Podcast and The Moth Radio Hour.</p>
